name: hashmap
description:
Construct a hashmap containing key-value associations of "<key> <value> ...".
Create hashmap literals via the {<key> <value> ...} syntax.
Hashmaps are applicable to a key to get their entry: (<hashmap> <key>)

name: hashmap-keys
description: Get the keys of <hashmap> as a list.

name: hashmap-values
description: Get the values of <hashmap> as a list.

name: hashmap-key?
description: Returns whether <obj> is a key in <hashmap>.

name: hashmap-set!
description:
Associate <value> to <key> in <hashmap>.
Returns whether replaced an existing value.

name: hashmap-delete!
description: Delete <key>'s association in <hashmap>. Returns whether succeeded.

name: hashmap-merge
description: Returns a new <hashmap> combining all of the associations in "<hashmap> ...".

name: hashmap-merge!
description: Combine all of the associations in "<merged-hashmap> ..." into <hashmap>.

name: hashcode
description:
Returns the hashcode of "<obj> ..." combined with one another.
Unused by any of the other hashmap primitives, but hey, it
could be useful to expose to users.
